summary: okay so i made that stranger things/detective pikachu au post a few days ago so here’s the semi-final Buddy List jonathan - per...
body:
okay so i made that stranger things/detective pikachu au post a few days ago so here’s the semi-final Buddy List

  • jonathan - per the plot of the movie, he doesn’t have one. thinking at the end he adopts like. an abandoned mightyena bc that’d be cool 
  • hopper - per the plot of the movie, pikachu 
  • nancy - houndoom 
  • will - squirtle 
  • joyce - very stressed psyduck. there’s also a family growlithe (@vacuum-fluorescent-display‘s wonderful idea!)
  • el - eevee, eventually evolves into a sylveon (idea from @asoue-sideblog, who also suggested kali’s) 
  • mike - vulpix 
  • lucas - also has a pikachu 
  • dustin - he DEFINITELY has a bulbasaur let’s be real 
  • max - litten, eventually evolves into a torracat. 
    • she’s one of the few characters who actively seeks out pokemon to train instead of just, you know, keeping pets, so she actually has quite a lot. but litten/torracat is her pokemon partner  
  • steve - charizard. he’s had him since he was a charmander and still treats him like a baby, even though he’s a giant flipping dragon 
  • kali - espeon 
  • we haven’t seen much of erica or robin so i hesitate to assign them a buddy yet however, i would love to see erica with a ponyta

summary:
MOVIE REVIEW: Detective Pikachu
#128
Ace detective Harry Goodman goes mysteriously missing, prompting his 21-year-old son, Tim,...
body:
MOVIE REVIEW: Detective Pikachu

#128

Ace detective Harry Goodman goes mysteriously missing, prompting his 21-year-old son, Tim, to find out what happened. Aiding in the investigation is Harry’s former Pokémon partner, wise-cracking, adorable super-sleuth Detective Pikachu. Finding that they are uniquely equipped to work together, as Tim is the only human who can talk with Pikachu, they join forces to unravel the tangled mystery.

I’m a huge pokemon fan ever since. I watched all episodes of it on TV and went toy hunting for pokemons. I was really happy to know that they will adapt the cartoon into live action and Ryan Reynolds to voice Pikachu. Movie was good. It has a simple story and all the pokemons were cute!!! Though some scenes were predictable, I was impressed that there was no Ash Ketchum in this film. I appreciated the originality of the story and the humor from the characters.

Rating: 3/5 for me

-Joe

body:
Detective Pikachu ya tiene fecha de lanzamiento en Blu-Ray y DVD (de momento en EE. UU.)

Detective Pikachu ha supuesto la primera incursión de la franquicia de monstruos de bolsillo en el mundo del cine de acción real y, habiendo partidarios y detractores, lo cierto es que no se puede negar que el universo construido en Rhyme City es el más acertado. Como con todo lanzamiento que llega al cine, más tarde lo hace al mundo de los reproductores domésticos, y ahora ya conocemos cuándo…

tags: SO MANY CUTE POKEMON CARDS IM DYING
summary: someone. anyone. help. pokemon cards...they’ve grabbed me and tossed me down a rabbit hole. that’s why they gave you the cards...
body:
someone. anyone. help.

pokemon cards…they’ve grabbed me and tossed me down a rabbit hole. that’s why they gave you the cards at the theater, man. they give you a little pikachu in a little hat with a little coffee mug, smiling all pretty at you with an attack called ‘coffee break.’ 

that’s how they get you. 

that cute, innocent smiling pikachu? he hides a devilish corporation inside, ready to steal your hard earned pennies away as you dive into mountains of debt made up of cute, stylish paper.

absolutely diabolical.
